<%= render 'layouts/navbar' %>

<header class="music-heading">
  <div class="intro-body">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto transparent-dark-container">
          <h2>My Music</h2>
          <p class="intro-text">
            Music has always been a large part of my life. Much like programming, music is a craft that you endlessly practise, improve and refine. There is always something new to master and
            it is always fun. From an early age, I found practising the piano was a way to unwind and escape for a while.
          </p>
          <p class="intro-text">
            Scroll down for a peek at some of my music projects to date.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <a href="#my" class="arrow js-scroll-trigger">
        <i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-o-down animated fa-4x"></i>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<section class="content-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-12 text-center">
        <h2 id="my">My Projects</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-5 text-center iframe-position">
        <div class="img-thumbnail">
          <h3>Bach's Prelude in C</h3>
          <div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9">
            <div id="YTvideo1"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="caption">
            <p>
              One of Bach's most well known and easily accessible preludes has made this piece a must learn for piano students. In addition to this, this piece is a popular choice for wedding ceremonies.</p>
            <p>
              Using <%= link_to 'Ableton', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ableton_Live', target: '_blank' %>, <%= link_to 'OBS', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_Broadcaster_Software', target: '_blank' %>, <%= link_to 'Synthesia', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Synthesia', target: '_blank' %> and <%= link_to 'GIMP', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GIMP', target: '_blank' %> I recorded my performance and put together a visual tutorial as to how it is played so the viewer can learn to play it for themselves. Have a little watch yourself.
            </p>
            <p>
              This video belongs to a separate YouTube channel of mine which is solely for Synthesia tutorials like this. <%= link_to 'Visit my Synthesia YouTube Channel', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gv-4Mk9xV7E&list=UUJCLykUyNiUHtK-2T6wjkow&index=1', target: '_blank' %> for more.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="img-thumbnail">
          <h3>Comptine D'un Autre Été</h3>
          <div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9">
            <iframe id="sc-player1" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/146506412&amp;color=%23060806&amp;hide_related=false&amp;show_comments=true&amp;show_user=true&amp;show_reposts=false&amp;show_teaser=true&amp;visual=true">
            </iframe>
          </div>
          <div class="caption">
            <p>
              Originally written by Yann Tiersen for the film Amélie (2001), Comptine D'un Autre Été remains to this day, an extremely popular piece. It's minimalist style has made this piece a popular choice to learn on the piano and a pleasant one to listen to. My soundcloud track alone has over a <strong>quarter of a million listens.</strong>
            </p>
            <p>
              I have also created a <%= link_to 'synthesia version of this piece', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5nExi3cezKg', target: '_blank' %>. You can <%= link_to 'visit my Soundcloud page', 'https://soundcloud.com/yamadaj2', target: '_blank' %> to listen to more of my piano solo tracks.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-lg-5 text-center iframe-position">
        <div class="img-thumbnail">
          <h3>Where Is My Mind?</h3>
          <div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9">
            <div id="YTvideo2"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="caption">
            <p>
              Originally written by The Pixies, this version is a cover of a cover by the pianist Maxence Cyrin. I first heard this piece in the TV show 'Mr. Robot' and I had to learn it straight away. Have a little watch if you like.
            </p>
            <p>
              This video belongs to a separate YouTube channel of mine which is solely for piano solo videos. <%= link_to 'Visit my Piano Solo YouTube Channel', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_pFmyxkRgWE&list=UUAiArHrQ_ypBh5ygHZWkyUA&index=2', target: '_blank' %> for more.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="container text-center">
  <%= link_to 'Back', root_path, class: "btn btn-default btn-lg" %>
</div>

